---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
const page = {
  title: "Mulch Color Guide | Edwards Landscape Group",
  description: "Choose the right mulch color and depth to refresh your beds, control weeds, and balance moisture."
};
---

<BaseLayout {...page}>
<main>
      <section
        class="page-hero article-hero"
        style="background-image: url('../images/Mulching_Service.jpg');"
        aria-label="Mulch color guide hero"
      >
        <div class="container">
          <div class="row align-items-end">
            <div class="col-lg-8 hero-content-block">
              <div class="hero-kicker">Landscape beds</div>
              <h1>Mulch color guide: picking the right finish for your beds</h1>
              <p class="article-subtitle">
                Fresh mulch protects plant roots, controls weeds, and sets the tone for your home’s curb appeal.
              </p>
              <div class="article-meta">
                <span>By Edwards Landscape Group</span>
                <span>&bull;</span>
                <span>Updated July 18, 2024</span>
                <span>&bull;</span>
                <span>5 min read</span>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="article-container" aria-labelledby="article-heading">
        <div class="container">
          <div class="article-layout">
            <aside class="article-toc" aria-label="On this page">
              <h2>Quick navigation</h2>
              <ol>
                <li><a href="#benefits">Why mulch matters</a></li>
                <li><a href="#colors">Choosing colors</a></li>
                <li><a href="#depth">How much to install</a></li>
                <li><a href="#timing">When to refresh</a></li>
              </ol>
            </aside>

            <article class="article-content" id="article-heading">
              <p>
                TruGreen-style mulching focuses on more than looks: consistent depth protects soil temperature, locks in
                moisture, and blocks weeds. Use this guide to pick a color and refresh schedule that fits your home and plantings.
              </p>

              <h2 id="benefits">1. Why mulch matters</h2>
              <ul class="checklist">
                <li>Prevents rapid soil temperature swings around roots.</li>
                <li>Stops sunlight from reaching weed seeds so they stay dormant.</li>
                <li>Reduces evaporation to keep irrigation costs down.</li>
              </ul>

              <h2 id="colors">2. Choosing colors</h2>
              <div class="tg-card-grid two-col">
                <div class="tg-card">
                  <h3>Natural brown</h3>
                  <p class="mb-0">Great for blending with wooded lots and brick facades.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="tg-card">
                  <h3>Classic black</h3>
                  <p class="mb-0">High contrast that makes evergreens and flowering plants pop.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="tg-card">
                  <h3>Rich red</h3>
                  <p class="mb-0">Bold color that pairs with lighter siding and stone.</p>
                </div>
              </div>

              <h2 id="depth">3. How much to install</h2>
              <p>
                We recommend a 2–3 inch depth for most beds. Going thicker can suffocate roots, while thinner layers break down too
                quickly to stop weeds.
              </p>

              <h2 id="timing">4. When to refresh</h2>
              <p>
                In Central Virginia, spring installations set you up for summer heat, while a light fall top-off keeps soil
                insulated through winter.
              </p>

              <div class="article-cta">
                <div>
                  <p class="eyebrow mb-1">Need a fresh layer?</p>
                  <h3 class="mb-2">Schedule mulch delivery and installation</h3>
                  <p class="mb-0">Pick your color and we'll handle bed prep, edging, and cleanup.</p>
                </div>
                <a class="btn btn-primary" href="../contact.html">Book mulching</a>
              </div>
            </article>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>
    </main>
</BaseLayout>
